    <string name="advanced_help">
         <![CDATA[
<h3>Advanced</h3>
    <p>Create or import your own stuff here.</p>

    <h4>Export game database to sd-card</h4>
    <p>All games in the game database can be exported to a single PGN file on sd-card. This file
        will be named chess.pgn and an existing file will be overwritten.</p>

    <h4>Import games into the game database</h4>
    <p>Use this option to add games to the game database. It lets you browse to a PGN file. Select
        and choose to import.</p>

    <h4>Delete all games in the game database</h4>
    <p>Use this option if you want to clean up the game database. Make sure you first make a backup
        to sd-card, this action can not be undone.</p>

    <h4>Create practice set</h4>
    <p>Creates practice positions from games that end in a check-mate. Browse to the file to
        process. Failed entries are usually games that did not end in a check-mate or are a
        duplicate</p>

    <h4>Reset practice set</h4>
    <p>Want to start over practicing? This will also reset your average time counter.</p>

        ]]>
    </string>
    <string name="online_help">
        <![CDATA[
        <p>
        <strong>FICS: Free Internet Chess Server</strong> lets you play with thousands of chess
        players online.<br/>
        Warning: if your device switches from one internet access point to another, the connection
        can break. There is no timeseal.<br/>
    </p>
    <h4>Menu</h4>
    <strong>Challenges</strong><br/>
    This shows players seeking a match. Click on the player in the list to accept a challenge.<br/>
    <strong>Seek</strong><br/>
    Set up your own challenge. If you fill in the handle of a player you know, it will make a direct
    challenge.<br/>
    <strong>Games</strong><br/>
    Watch games being played online. A grandmaster can be identified by the GM prefix to the handle.<br/>
    <strong>Players</strong><br/>
    Shows idle players with ratings.<br/>
         ]]>
    </string>

